HEADWORD: Woolsack
<hw>Wool"sack`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sack or bag of
wool; specifically, the seat of the lord chancellor of England in the
House of Lords, being a large, square sack of wool resembling a divan in
form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woolsey</ent>⟦br⟧
